title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Veterans Memorial Coliseum on 1990-03-28
description:
Set 1	Cold Rain & Snow > New Minglewood Blues % Easy To Love You % High Time % Queen Jane Approximately % Loose Lucy % Cassidy > Deal 

Set 2	Foolish Heart > Looks Like Rain > Cumberland Blues > The Weight ; Hey Pocky Way > Drums > Space > The Other One > Wharf Rat > Good Lovin' 

Encore	Revolution

reviews.review_text: keep it on the DL mp3 vbr ;)

best DL-able recording of this show I cast my vote for this version of the show as the best one.

A close second it the Mattes/Miller, but it is too silent for my taste. Great warmth, but it needs a simple amplitude factor change.

The third best recording of this night is the Mendel one, but it has slightly too much audience noise IMO. 

This recording is pretty solid, but somewhat too sharp. However, it's the one I downloaded. The pictures are a nice bonus as well.

4 stars for show, 4 for recording.

Beautiful Work, Dan... So, I'm doing this project on twitter called #DeadOnThisDate, and I'm working a couple of days ahead, and Knick '90 grabs be, and "Oh, the Nassaua Awesome was this year, too!" 
Opened ALL Archive files for this date and start listening. 
I'm an old Union Stagehand, I have ear. 
A lot of recordings using a sheet of wax, a safety pin, and a rolled show program. i have a case full of the tapes I purchased.
No. Next.
No. Next.
No. Next.
OH!!!! WHAAAT!!! Holy f*ck, this recording is inside my mind before the first notes of "Cold Rain And Snow" even started. 
That Gorramed mix is inside my head! 
JEEEEE-BUSSS that's the most aggressively focused and tuned MATRIX I've yet heard. I stopped. Nine other files get the side-eye. This mix is life-changing. 
Dan, I suspect this mix either came SUPER easy, or DAYS AND NIGHTS of figiting this right, but you boy howdy, you NAILED it. Bravo Zulu. 
My skull is smoking proper!

Needless to say, this is the DOTD Feature for the day.
